description: From Middle English hory, hoory, from Old English horiġ, horhiġ (“foul, unclean”), from Proto-West Germanic *hurhwīg, from Proto-Germanic *hurhwīgaz (“foul, filthy, soiled, unclean”). Cognate with Middle High German horwig, horwic, horig, horg (“muddy, filthy”).

adjectives.description: horry (comparative horrier or more horry, superlative horriest or most horry)

entries.meaning: (now chiefly dialectal) impure; unclean; disgustingly dirty; foul
